article.headline: San Diego State 119, Campbell 82
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Lorenzo Wade scored a career-high 21 points as San Diego State defeated Campbell 119-82 Tuesday. Brandon Heath and Mohammed Abukar each added 19 points as the Aztecs snapped a two-game losing streak. San Diego State (9-2) topped the 100-point mark for the first time since Dec. 2, 1998 with its fourth highest point total in the school's Division I history. The Aztecs took the lead for good at 26-25 at the 9:37 mark in the first half. Wade then led the team on a 16-4 run in the final four minutes for a commanding 58-42 halftime lead. He had 10 points in the run, including a 3-pointer with 1.1 seconds left. Jonathan Rodriguez scored 19 points and Reggie Bishop added 14 for the Flying Camels (3-3).
